It seems you are trying to loop through the children of the dataSnapshot and create TextViews for each child's key and value. You want to show them in the layout of the activity, but there's no code for adding these TextViews to the layout.

To fix this, first, add a LinearLayout container inside your activity_result.xml file where you will add these TextViews dynamically.

```xml
<LinearLayout
    android:id="@+id/container"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
    android:orientation="vertical"
    android:focusableInTouchMode="true"
    ...>
</LinearLayout>
```

Then, in your Result.java class file inside the onDataChange() method, get a reference to this LinearLayout container, and add the created TextViews to it.

```java
@Override
public void onDataChange(@NonNull DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {

    // Get a reference to the LinearLayout container
    LinearLayout container = findViewById(R.id.container);

    // Clear the container for previous data
    container.removeAllViews();

    for (DataSnapshot childSnapshot : dataSnapshot.getChildren()) {
        String name = childSnapshot.getKey();
        String data = childSnapshot.getValue().toString();

        TextView nameTextView = new TextView(Result.this);
        nameTextView.setText(name);
        // Add any TextView attributes you need here

        TextView dataTextView = new TextView(Result.this);
        dataTextView.setText(data);
        // Add any TextView attributes you need here

        // Add the TextViews to the container
        container.addView(nameTextView);
        container.addView(dataTextView);
    }

}
```

This should add the TextViews with the data to the LinearLayout container in your layout.

